article.description: — Kenny Strawbridge had 17 points as Alabama State topped Jackson State 72-57 on Saturday.
article.headline: Strawbridge leads Alabama St. over Jackson St. 72-57
article.linkText: Strawbridge leads Alabama St. over Jackson St. 72-57
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- — Kenny Strawbridge had 17 points as Alabama State topped Jackson State 72-57 on Saturday. Strawbridge converted all 11 of his free throws. DJ Jackson had 13 points for Alabama State (4-12, 2-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Isaiah Range added 10 points. Alabama State scored 22 points in the first half, a season low for the team. Chance Moore scored a career-high 21 points for the Tigers (2-11, 0-2), whose losing streak reached five games. Jayveous McKinnis added 14 points. Terence Lewis II had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
